        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:56PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 656 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Buckner to near Fouke.
Movement was southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Magnolia, Stamps, Waldo, Lewisville, McNeil, Fouke,
Bradley, Taylor, Buckner, Garland, Willisville, Bodcaw, Bussey,
Smithland, Genoa, Brightstar, Canfield, Village, and Macedonia.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
